    <div class=header>
        <h2>What is a Tsunami</h2>
    </div>

    <div class=content>
        <p>A tsunami is a series of enormous waves caused by large-scale disturbances
            in or near oceans, such as earthquakes, volcanic eruptions, underwater
            landslides, or meteorite impacts. These waves can travel across entire
            ocean basins at high speeds, causing widespread damage when they reach
            coastal areas. The average height of a tsunami is 100ft above sea level. The tallest tsunami occured in 1958
            in Alaska, where it reached an initial height of 1700ft. The term "tsunami" originates from Japanese, with
            "tsu" meaning "harbor" and "nami" meaning "wave."</p>
    </div>

